The camera is for what?

265
00:23:03.467 --> 00:23:05.802
You know what? I c…
I can't even get into it.

266
00:23:10.807 --> 00:23:12.869
You know. I've been
to widow's bay before.

267
00:23:12.893 --> 00:23:15.312
For fuck's sake. it was nice
to order a cappuccino for once.

268
00:23:16.897 --> 00:23:18.249
Yes.

269
00:23:18.273 --> 00:23:19.417
Tha… thank you.

270
00:23:19.441 --> 00:23:20.668
God.

271
00:23:20.692 --> 00:23:22.528
Feels good to hear someone say that.

272
00:23:24.488 --> 00:23:26.549
So… so what brings you here this time?

273
00:23:26.573 --> 00:23:28.760
I work for a structural engineering firm.

274
00:23:28.784 --> 00:23:31.471
- City hired us to inspect the dock.
- Right.

275
00:23:31.495 --> 00:23:33.431
Yeah. For the expansion.

276
00:23:33.455 --> 00:23:36.291
Yeah. Looks like you're expecting
a lot more ferries out here?

277
00:23:36.792 --> 00:23:37.876
It's the hope.

278
00:23:38.377 --> 00:23:40.188
Well. that's a lot on your shoulders.

279
00:23:40.212 --> 00:23:42.130
I'm sure your constituents are excited.

280
00:23:44.174 --> 00:23:45.175
No?

281
00:23:46.552 --> 00:23:47.761
They don't make it easy.

282
00:23:48.720 --> 00:23:51.032
Well. they must appreciate you some.

283
00:23:51.056 --> 00:23:52.474
They voted you in as mayor.

284
00:23:55.102 --> 00:23:56.895
I ran uncontested.

285
00:23:59.022 --> 00:24:00.274
That's embarrassing. Tom.

286
00:24:05.320 --> 00:24:07.197
All right. Testing my luck.

287
00:24:09.491 --> 00:24:12.387
- No. No.
- Okay. Here we go.

288
00:24:12.411 --> 00:24:15.122
"Daddy's younger boss
yelled at him today."

289
00:24:16.206 --> 00:24:17.291
- What?
- What?

290
00:24:18.208 --> 00:24:19.936
Now I gotta go back three spaces.

291
00:24:19.960 --> 00:24:23.255
- All right. You're up. There you go.
- Okay.

292
00:24:23.922 --> 00:24:26.175
"Roll… roll to see if
the neighbor is home."

293
00:24:27.384 --> 00:24:28.385
Come on. neighbor.

294
00:24:29.595 --> 00:24:31.030
Yes!

295
00:24:31.054 --> 00:24:32.448
Saved by the neighbor.

296
00:24:32.472 --> 00:24:34.075
One. Two. Three. Four.

297
00:24:34.099 --> 00:24:35.160
Thanks. man.

298
00:24:35.184 --> 00:24:36.977
Here we go.

299
00:24:37.853 --> 00:24:39.247
"Daddy had a bad day.

300
00:24:39.271 --> 00:24:41.690
- "Go back six spaces."
- Man. I'm in the basement.

301
00:24:43.108 --> 00:24:44.610
I'm getting crushed.

302
00:24:48.697 --> 00:24:50.550
Yeah. he was a local.

303
00:24:50.574 --> 00:24:52.576
My mom was from the mainland.

304
00:24:53.410 --> 00:24:55.430
They met when she
was on a schooner tour.

305
00:24:56.538 --> 00:24:59.017
But she certainly couldn't
make it work with him.

306
00:24:59.041 --> 00:25:02.729
So. I grew up in. I grew
up in Massachusetts.

307
00:25:02.753 --> 00:25:04.755
But I spent my summers here.

308
00:25:07.049 --> 00:25:09.027
I used to dread those summers.

309
00:25:09.051 --> 00:25:10.528
- Really?
- Yeah.

310
00:25:10.552 --> 00:25:11.929
How bad was he?

311
00:25:14.598 --> 00:25:15.599
I mean…

312
00:25:17.309 --> 00:25:18.703
Not the worst guy in the world.

313
00:25:18.727 --> 00:25:22.457
Just a lot of… walking
on egg shells. you know?

314
00:25:22.481 --> 00:25:23.649
I do.

315
00:25:24.733 --> 00:25:26.860
Didn't talk much once I got older.

316
00:25:27.569 --> 00:25:29.029
Moved back when he got sick.

317
00:25:29.988 --> 00:25:30.989
Met my wife.

318
00:25:31.990 --> 00:25:33.200
Rest is history.

319
00:25:34.243 --> 00:25:36.095
Guy's lucky you came back at all.

320
00:25:36.119 --> 00:25:37.120
Yeah.

321
00:25:42.668 --> 00:25:45.730
You know. just a lot of the times he
would come home after a couple of drinks.

322
00:25:45.754 --> 00:25:47.005
spewing these…

323
00:25:49.466 --> 00:25:52.654
Just these horror
stories about the island.

324
00:25:52.678 --> 00:25:54.012
I mean shit I was…

325
00:25:54.513 --> 00:25:56.014
I was way too young to hear.

326
00:25:59.268 --> 00:26:00.978
The guy never should've had a kid.

327
00:26:05.190 --> 00:26:07.192
He called me soft when I was six.

328
00:26:13.866 --> 00:26:18.120
I always said. you know. the only thing
this island's cursed with is alcoholism.

329
00:26:21.874 --> 00:26:23.125
You gotta be careful.

330
00:26:24.877 --> 00:26:27.296
They'll drag you down
with them if you let 'em.

331
00:26:29.089 --> 00:26:33.552
Fuckin' useless ass-backwards.
small brained. townie Hicks.

332
00:26:34.720 --> 00:26:39.474
Let 'em all rot in hell and
watch 'em all fucking burn.

333
00:26:47.357 --> 00:26:48.692
I may have had too much to drink.

334
00:26:54.281 --> 00:26:57.326
Listen. I know two things to be true.

335
00:26:57.826 --> 00:26:59.745
One. you're a great mayor.

336
00:27:00.370 --> 00:27:01.455
No. no. no.

337
00:27:03.332 --> 00:27:04.684
I know these things.

338
00:27:04.708 --> 00:27:05.709
And two.

339
00:27:06.919 --> 00:27:09.272
there's no such thing
as ghosts. All right?

340
00:27:09.296 --> 00:27:11.107
There's no… what was it?

341
00:27:11.131 --> 00:27:12.299
"Harriet Fitzgerald"?

342
00:27:12.883 --> 00:27:14.468
- Hortence.
- Well. okay.

343
00:27:15.052 --> 00:27:17.614
No hortence is going to
appear in your window.

344
00:27:17.638 --> 00:27:20.867
You know. the killer sea
captain. the new year's party.

345
00:27:20.891 --> 00:27:22.559
the "murder clown." I mean…

346
00:27:23.936 --> 00:27:27.731
Maybe all those things were real at
one point. but they're not anymore.

347
00:27:28.315 --> 00:27:29.316
So…

348
00:27:30.317 --> 00:27:32.069
All right. To bed.

349
00:27:33.237 --> 00:27:34.446
I say.

350
00:27:35.447 --> 00:27:38.450
you finish off their little checklist
and show 'em who's in charge.

351
00:27:39.368 --> 00:27:40.369
Cheers.

352
00:27:41.411 --> 00:27:42.579
Cheers.

353
00:27:45.749 --> 00:27:47.376
Well. probably best.

354
00:27:48.168 --> 00:27:49.837
Okay. All right.

355
00:27:50.504 --> 00:27:51.606
Have a good one.

356
00:27:51.630 --> 00:27:52.798
- Night.
- Night.

357
00:27:59.346 --> 00:28:00.347
I'm good.

358
00:29:33.649 --> 00:29:36.151
I am in the crawl space.

359
00:29:43.909 --> 00:29:44.910
Hello?

360
00:29:50.707 --> 00:29:51.959
William?

361
00:29:56.004 --> 00:29:57.089
William?

362
00:30:03.011 --> 00:30:04.012
Howdy. neighbor.

363
00:30:05.347 --> 00:30:07.808
Wha… why didn't you answer me?

364
00:30:14.565 --> 00:30:15.959
Need some help in there?

365
00:30:15.983 --> 00:30:18.110
What? No! No.

366
00:30:18.861 --> 00:30:20.630
No. don't… don't… don't come in.

367
00:30:20.654 --> 00:30:21.756
Don't… I'm coming out!

368
00:30:21.780 --> 00:30:23.407
Don't come in! Don't come…

369
00:30:27.953 --> 00:30:29.329
No!

370
00:30:42.009 --> 00:30:43.153
I locked the door myself.

371
00:30:43.177 --> 00:30:45.488
Whoever it was would've
had to have had a key. Tom.

372
00:30:45.512 --> 00:30:46.513
What…

373
00:30:47.264 --> 00:30:48.265
He's…

374
00:30:49.016 --> 00:30:50.994
Did you see something? You…

375
00:30:51.018 --> 00:30:52.954
You didn't see anyone
in the crawl space?

376
00:30:52.978 --> 00:30:54.706
Well. does my demeanor suggest

377
00:30:54.730 --> 00:30:56.899
that I just engaged with
someone inside a crawl space?

378
00:30:58.066 --> 00:30:59.067
Hold on.

379
00:31:11.079 --> 00:31:14.750
I don't understand. Now
look… maybe I was… I was…

380
00:31:15.250 --> 00:31:16.311
Sleepwalking?

381
00:31:16.335 --> 00:31:17.336
I know. My…

382
00:31:17.836 --> 00:31:19.689
He said his name was William.

383
00:31:19.713 --> 00:31:20.797
Willy.

384
00:31:21.548 --> 00:31:22.966
The clown.

385
00:31:23.675 --> 00:31:24.885
That's who you got?

386
00:31:25.511 --> 00:31:26.678
You saw something.

387
00:31:27.846 --> 00:31:32.059
You saw something and you're
still gonna let folks stay here.

388
00:31:32.809 --> 00:31:34.662
- Don't you start with this shit. wyck.
- No.

389
00:31:34.686 --> 00:31:36.915
- Don't you raise your voice at me.
- Shit. Every cent I have

390
00:31:36.939 --> 00:31:39.125
- I put into this inn!
- I'm telling you this place is a trap!

391
00:31:39.149 --> 00:31:40.502
It's not!

392
00:31:40.526 --> 00:31:42.212
It's perfectly fine.

393
00:31:42.236 --> 00:31:44.404
Then you go in the captain's suite.

394
00:31:46.615 --> 00:31:47.616
Kurt. just…

395
00:31:49.493 --> 00:31:53.330
Just go into the room and show
him there's nothing to be afraid of.

396
00:31:55.916 --> 00:31:58.085
There. See?

397
00:31:59.169 --> 00:32:00.170
Inside.

398
00:32:00.796 --> 00:32:03.924
- What?
- Go inside and close the door.

399
00:32:05.217 --> 00:32:07.261
We're gonna… we're gonna count to ten.

400
00:32:13.642 --> 00:32:15.370
One. two. three. four. five.

401
00:32:15.394 --> 00:32:17.312
six. seven. eight. nine. ten.

402
00:32:18.689 --> 00:32:20.542
What the fuck? I thought
we said ten seconds?

403
00:32:20.566 --> 00:32:21.709
Well. that was ten.

404
00:32:21.733 --> 00:32:23.485
How long do you
think you were in there?

405
00:32:25.988 --> 00:32:28.800
- Ten seconds.
- Then why don't you go back in for 30?

406
00:32:28.824 --> 00:32:30.593
Can I at least have some food first?

407
00:32:30.617 --> 00:32:32.619
The fuck you need
food for 30 seconds for?

408
00:32:38.709 --> 00:32:42.522
Loftis. you know there's
something wrong with this island.

409
00:32:42.546 --> 00:32:45.382
You've seen it with
your own two eyes now.

410
00:32:46.133 --> 00:32:47.176
Come on. son.

411
00:32:48.135 --> 00:32:49.821
You're right here with me.

412
00:32:49.845 --> 00:32:51.096
Seeing what I'm seeing.

413
00:32:53.390 --> 00:32:54.933
You can call it off right now.

414
00:32:58.937 --> 00:33:00.039
No. I can't.

415
00:33:00.063 --> 00:33:01.148
We can.

416
00:33:02.191 --> 00:33:05.503
It's not right to bring
anyone here. you know it.

417
00:33:05.527 --> 00:33:06.921
Island's awake now.

418
00:33:06.945 --> 00:33:08.405
It's dangerous.

419
00:33:08.989 --> 00:33:09.990
All right.

420
00:33:16.246 --> 00:33:17.247
All set?

421
00:33:36.308 --> 00:33:38.268
What the hell is this?

422
00:33:44.316 --> 00:33:45.734
This black mold?

423
00:33:50.447 --> 00:33:51.573
Mold.

424
00:33:54.034 --> 00:33:56.513
Well. that's it. you must have
hallucinated from exposure.

425
00:33:56.537 --> 00:33:57.538
No.

426
00:33:58.080 --> 00:33:59.414
No.

427
00:34:00.624 --> 00:34:04.771
You think you could get
affected that quickly? No.

428
00:34:04.795 --> 00:34:08.066
That can be remediated
in 72 hours. Tom.

429
00:34:08.090 --> 00:34:11.009
And I will still seal up this
suite for good measure.

430
00:34:16.473 --> 00:34:17.641
Loftis.

431
00:34:49.840 --> 00:34:50.841
How'd it go?

432
00:34:51.592 --> 00:34:52.592
Fine.
